description:
**Essential Job Functions**

· Ensure compliance to regulations for all referrals;

· Participate in onboarding appointments for accepted participants.

· Manage assigned case load of accepted participants;

· Facilitate Case Management meetings at least monthly;

· Provide assistance with obtaining/maintaining any Federal, State, and local benefits and provision of SOAR benefits applications;

· Educate participants on their housing rights;

· Provide life skills training as needed in order to maintain permanent housing including money management and home maintenance;

· Transport residents to view apartments; advocate on resident’s behalf with prospective landlords; must use own personal vehicle when agency vehicle is unavailable;

· Provide or refer to support services designed to stabilize households in permanent, habitable housing;

· Facilitate program graduations.

· Coordinate all aspects of utility and rental arrears payments, rental assistance payments, and other eligible financial assistance.

· Complete 3-month income eligibility reviews for assigned case load.

· Research permanent housing opportunities and maintain housing resource database.

· Coordinate all aspects of participants movement to alternative housing;

· Complete habitability inspections;

· Coordinate lease signings;

· Execute Security Deposits and Repayment Agreements.

· Manage outstanding Security Deposit repayments including monthly invoicing and incoming payments.

· Provide aftercare services to graduates consisting of contact with participants at least monthly for six months following graduation from the program.

· Required to be ambulatory and present and able to perform all job functions without limitations, up to and including life preservation activities.

· Responsible to comply with all Agency Policies including Agency Code of Conduct and Confidentiality Policies, Medicaid Compliance Program and Protocols and Justice Center Code of Conduct.

· Maintain attendance and punctuality. Notify supervisor when late or absent. Provide adequate notice when scheduling time off.

**Job Duties include but are not limited to:**

· Orient, train and supervise assigned staff including preparation of staff evaluations and interviewing prospective candidates for staff positions.

· Attend and participate in staff meetings, training sessions and other relevant meetings as scheduled.

· Develop and maintain relationships with local realtors and landlords.

· Participate in HMIS reporting and SOAR certification.

· Report to Support Services Supervisor.

Job Type: Full-time

Pay: $27.30 per hour

Education:

* High school or equivalent (Required)

License/Certification:

* New York State Driver's License (Preferred)

Work Location: In person

**DISTINGUISHING FEATURES OF THE CLASS:**

This position is responsible for planning, coordinating and supervising all aspects of the School Food Service Program at a small secondary school. The work includes management of school cafeterias and providing or monitoring alternate menus for breakfast, lunch and/or after school snacks to the student body and faculty. The incumbent has the added responsibility for administering the send-out-food program which provides menu items, baked goods and other specialty foods to a large number of secondary schools. While the ability to exercise independent judgement and make independent decisions is a requirement, general supervision is received from administrative personnel. General supervision is exercised over assigned personnel. Does related work as required.

**TYPICAL WORK ACTIVITIES: (Illustrative only)**

* Supervises the preparation and serving of breakfast, lunch and after school snacks for students and faculty;
* Supervises and coordinates the preparation, service, distribution, and/or receiving of all food items prepared at the school for other secondary schools;
* Oversees and monitors all restricted menus for students with special dietary needs;
* Maintains and completes preparation reports for both the secondary and the elementary send-out program;
* Submits requisition sheets, via computer, for food items and supplies for all aspects of the program at the school;
* Checks in food items and supplies received;
* Monitors performance of Food Service Helpers, Cooks and Bakers; Prepares employee schedules and time sheets;
* Assists in the planning and pricing of menus for the school system; Keeps electronic and written records and prepares required reports;
* Maintains highest approved standards of nutrition, safety and sanitation through supervision of the preparation of foods.

**FULL PERFORMANCE KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS, ABILITIES AND PERSONAL CHARACTERISTICS:**

* Thorough knowledge of kitchen equipment, quantity food preparation and cafeteria operating practices;
* good knowledge of safety and sanitation procedures; good knowledge of foods and principles of nutrition;
* ability to plan and supervise the work of others;
* ability to effectively operate a computer;
* ability to keep records and prepare required reports;
* ability to communicate effectively;
* ability to maintain effective working relationships; tact; courtesy; resourcefulness; good judgment;
* physical condition commensurate with the demands of the position.

**MINIMUM QUALIFICATION: EITHER**

A) Graduation from a regionally accredited or New York State registered four year college or university with a Bachelor's Degree and at least 12 credit hours in nutrition or a related subject, as well as one (1) year of experience in large quantity food preparation for a school food service program, restaurant or institution; or

B) Graduation from a regionally accredited or New York State registered two year college or university with an Associate's Degree and at least 6 credit hours in nutrition or a related subject, as well as three (3) years of experience as described in (A); or

C) An equivalent combination of education/training and experience as defined by the limits of (A) and (B).

**CLASSIFICATION: COMPETITIVE** (Civil Service Tested Position)

Job Types: Full-time, Part-time

Pay: $46,152.00 - $61,556.00 per year

Benefits:

* Flexible schedule

Schedule:

* Day shift

Experience:

* Food preparation: 1 year (Required)
* Supervisory: 1 year (Required)

Ability to Commute:

* Yonkers, NY (Required)

Work Location: In person

Human Resources Receptionist  


This is a great opportunity to start a career in Human Resources! Alliance is an employee owned company and we are looking for a motivated, cheerful, upbeat candidate with the ability to interact with our employees, clients and vendors to ensure their satisfaction. Ability to prioritize workload and willingness to ensure that all deadlines are met are essential to this position. This position does require candidates to be Bilingual/Spanish.  



**Responsibilities:**  

* Handle employee inquiries and providing an appropriate response in timely manner;
* Establish and maintain a positive relationship with our employees as well as corporate office staff;
* Organize and maintain electronic and paper files;
* Perform basic office functions, such as scanning, faxing, filing and data entry;
* Prepare and maintain standard and ad hoc reports and queries;
* Handling inquiries and providing an appropriate response in timely manner;
* Provide clerical and administrative support;
* Compose and distribute routine written correspondence;
* Handle front desk responsibilities, heavy phone volume and greeting vistors.



**Requirements:**  

* 1- 2 years’ receptionist or customer service experience;  

Excellent computer skills;
* Excellent interpersonal skills and etiquette;
* Attention to detail and exceptional listening ability;
* Ability to multi-task effectively and efficiently;
* Analytical and logical, with ability to identify problems, recommend solutions and follow up on results;
* Ability to work in fast-paced work environment;
* Bilingual/Spanish.


We want you to join the Alliance Team!  



Alliance Building Services is an Equal Opportunity Employer committed to hiring a diverse workforce.  

EOE/Minorities/Females/Vet/Disability **Alliance Building Services, a prestigious leader in the building service industry a customer service minded professional to join our Corporate Offices.**  

**Our Receptionist will provide information and assistance to our employees, clients and vendors.** **Pay range: $22 to $25 per hour**
